-- Judge Denies Motion to Intervene in Empire State Building Suit
-- B y   C h r i s   D o l m e t s c h
-- 2013-02-21T16:11:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-21/judge-denies-motion-to-intervene-in-empire-state-building-suit.html
A  New York  judge denied a motion by
a group led by Andrew Penson to intervene in a case over efforts
to include the Empire State Building in a real estate investment
trust that would go public. The judge permitted the group to
participate on a limited basis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Dolmetsch in New York State Supreme Court in  Manhattan  at  cdolmetsch@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
